CHANGELOG.md:15:- Wired `GenerationQueue` into the generation pipeline: updated its constructor to accept pipeline dependencies (`client`, `cache`, `budget`, `storage`) and implemented a `process_one()` method acting as a single-iteration worker loop that dequeues an item, generates audio, stores it, and marks the job done or failed. Added an integration test to verify the end-to-end processing pipeline on a mock client and storage.
CHANGELOG.md:17:- Added generation queue claim transitions: `GenerationQueue.dequeue()` now atomically claims the oldest queued row in a single SQLite transaction, marks it `running`, increments `attempts`, and refreshes `updated_at`; `mark_done()` completes running items; and `mark_failed()` requeues transient failures until the retry budget is exhausted, then marks the item `failed`. New queue tests cover FIFO claim ordering, retry-on-failure, terminal failure, timestamp refreshes, and concurrent no-double-claim behavior.
